    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Open any untrusted site with HTTPS connection using Firefox Focus (for example, https://badssl.com/ and choose any \"dangerous\" link)\r\n2. Skip notification \"Secure Connection Failed\" by tapping on \"Accept the Risk and Continue\"\r\n3. Look at the security icon and status\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nFirefox Focus defines connection as unsecure even with security exception, like Firefox for Desktop\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nFirefox for Android defines connection and site's certificate as fully secure and misleads the user\r\n### Device information\r\n\r\n* Android device: Samsung Galaxy A20s (ARM64) with Android 10\r\n* Focus version: 8.16.0 (Build #351481538 \ud83e\udd8e 89.0-20210527174632)\r\n## Video\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/85299944/120746585-2ec4ed00-c508-11eb-9e69-45dbd4f12c36.mp4\r\n",
